Class CardCollection

java.lang.Object
  comp125.CardCollection

public class CardCollection
extends java.lang.Object

A CardCollection is a set of cards. It is possible to have multiple instances of the same kind of card in the set. For example, a set may have two Ace of Clubs.

public int binarySearch(Card target)
TO BE COMPLETED implement binary search based on Card.compareTo(Card) to look for a target card. if target.compareto(cards[mid]) == 0, return mid if target.compareto(cards[mid]) < 0, look in left half if target.compareto(cards[mid]) == 0, look in right half
